    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for FDA GCBP hemolysis CFD model at MRL 5",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol global sensitivity analysis (N=4096 quasi-random LHS samples) was performed varying eight model inputs — inlet flow rate (3.5–6.0 L/min), impeller rotational speed (2000–3500 RPM), blood viscosity (3.2–4.8 mPa·s), power-law hemolysis exponent alpha (0.62–0.82), hemolysis coefficient C (1.8e-6 to 3.5e-6), gap clearance (0.15–0.35 mm), turbulence model constant C_mu (0.07–0.11), and inlet hematocrit (35–45%). The dominant first-order contributors to variance in predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) were the hemolysis exponent alpha (S1=0.38), impeller speed (S1=0.27), and gap clearance (S1=0.19); total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions beyond alpha-speed coupling (ST-S1 < 0.04 for all factors). The analysis informed tightened priors for Bayesian UQ and confirmed that the model output is most sensitive to the constitutive hemolysis law parameters, motivating the targeted experimental calibration documented in VR-03.",
    "method": "Variance-based Sobol indices (Saltelli 2010 estimator), N=4096 quasi-random LHS, 8 factors, 36864 model evaluations total",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "hemolysis exponent alpha",
      "impeller rotational speed",
      "gap clearance"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 4096
  },
