      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "In-scope domain constraint for FDA GCBP hemolysis CFD model",
      "description": "The model is applicable only to centrifugal blood pumps with impeller tip diameter between 35 mm and 55 mm, operating with human whole blood (hematocrit 35–45%, temperature 35–38 °C) in the flow rate range 3.5–6.0 L/min and rotational speed 2000–3500 RPM. Application outside these bounds — including axial-flow pumps, pediatric devices, or non-Newtonian blood substitutes — is explicitly out of scope. The model has not been validated for pulsatile inlet boundary conditions or for devices incorporating magnetic levitation bearings."
    },
